g.text: UML Diagram: Class DescriptorValueDomain in Context
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: • Descriptor: Use of a code for variable identification in the context of a data structure and a variable descriptor component.
a.xlink:title: • Descriptor: Use of a code for variable identification in the context of a data structure and a variable descriptor component.

a.title: • DescriptorVariable: Variable that provides codes for variable identification in the context of a data structure. Variable playing the role of a variable descriptor component.
a.xlink:title: • DescriptorVariable: Variable that provides codes for variable identification in the context of a data structure. Variable playing the role of a variable descriptor component.

a.title: • DimensionComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a dimensional data structure to identify the universes associated with data points. The variable acts as a field in the compound identifier (the key structure) to disambiguate the cells in the multi-dimensional "cube".
a.xlink:title: • DimensionComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a dimensional data structure to identify the universes associated with data points. The variable acts as a field in the compound identifier (the key structure) to disambiguate the cells in the multi-dimensional "cube".

a.title: • InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.
a.xlink:title: • InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.

a.title: • ValueDomain: Set of permissible values for a variable (adapted from ISO/IEC 11179).
a.xlink:title: • ValueDomain: Set of permissible values for a variable (adapted from ISO/IEC 11179).

a.title: • CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: • CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: • LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.
a.xlink:title: • LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.

a.title: • Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: • Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: • RepresentedVariable: Conceptual variable with a substantive value domain specified.
a.xlink:title: • RepresentedVariable: Conceptual variable with a substantive value domain specified.

a.title: • MainKeyMember: Identifies the unit of interest, either a statistical unit or a population, via identifier or dimension components, respectively, plus an optional contextual component. If neither identifier nor dimension components are present, then a synthetic id component is used.
